<BaseLayout title="About — Rhys Murray">
  <h1>About</h1>
  <p>
    I'm Rhys, a software engineer in Brisbane. I've been working with Ruby for about ten years,
    starting with the Ruby track at Launch School back in 2016.
  </p>
  <p>
    My first development work came through a secondment at SkyMesh, where I automated internal
    processes and built debt collection and customer information tooling. From there I joined Cohort Go,
    which was acquired by <a href="https://www.flywire.com">Flywire</a> during my time there. I went
    from Junior DevOps and Automation Engineer through to Senior Software Engineer across those two
    companies.
  </p>
  <p>
    I moved to <a href="https://www.tanda.co">Tanda</a> to be closer to decision making again.
    Flywire was US-based and the distance made that harder than I wanted. At Tanda I lead the
    Payroll team.
  </p>
  <p>
    In my spare time I build <a href="https://theysaidyes.rsvp">theysaidyes.rsvp</a>, a wedding
    RSVP platform that shows up in a few posts on this blog.
  </p>
